{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"03d2ec67-66a3-4415-a38f-2fcf28f4ecb6","content":"There's no pipeline file in the workspace, so here's the general migration guidance:\n\n## Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test` + CLI flags\n\n**Before (VSTest@3):**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform):**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: Run tests\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --no-build\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      -- \n      --report-trx\n      --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: Publish TRX results\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: Publish code coverage\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **Enable the new platform** — add this property to each test `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   ```\n2. **TRX reports** — use `--report-trx` (replaces the old built-in TRX from VSTest). Add the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` NuGet package.\n3. **Code coverage** — use `--coverage` (built into .NET 8+). Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` if needed.\n4. **Publish tasks** — `VSTest@3` auto-published results; now you need explicit `PublishTestResults@2` and `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` steps with `condition: always()` so results are published even on failure.\n\nArguments after `--` are passed to Microsoft.Testing.Platform; arguments before go to `dotnet test`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2b392cc0-1396-4d83-87d7-f1962f3c0efa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking a general guidance question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":639,"requestId":"A02D:17D0EF:C49B2C:E50796:69FE85BD"},"id":"b91123c5-8921-428d-8929-1145ebf40195","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:54:32.981Z","parentId":"2e7d58cc-e9b5-4763-8869-a97a000960e9"}
